WELCOME TO OUR COMMUNITY WEBSITE

If you wish to add your club’s details to our website, publicise your event or contribute ideas or information please contact the Clerk.  The links and telephone numbers are checked regularly, but please advise the Clerk if any of the information is incorrect.

Mrs Tracey Paine
Clerk and Responsible Financial Officer
Colehill Parish Council
‘Inglewood’
15 Greenclose Lane
WIMBORNE
BH21 2AL

Telephone: 01202 900821
Email: clerk@colehill.gov.uk

Colehill Parish Council is not responsible for the content of web pages from other organisations on this site. 

GRANT AID

The Council issues Grant Aid every April. Organisations must apply by 6 September 2019. For more information and to download an application form go to the grants page.

 

You can now follow us on Twitter and like us on Facebook

Our Tweets

                                                   

Colehill Girlguiding is looking for adult support for their Guide Unit which meets on Tuesday evenings & also for their Brownie Unit which meets on Thursdays, early evening. Info available at: girlguiding.org.uk/get-involv… or email: GirlguidingColehillDistrict@hotmail.com pic.twitter.com/590J7vyaj2

About 10 hours ago

We are holding a drop-in afternoon on Saturday 23 March, from 1pm to 3.30pm, at Colehill Memorial Hall (Committee Room), for people who would like to find out how to become a parish councillor. We hope you will be able to join us. pic.twitter.com/o1aUFwoeww

About 10 hours ago

The Community Heartbeat Trust has confirmed that the Parish Council's defibrillator at The Reef, Colehill Lane, has now been registered with the ambulance service. That means there are 3 defibrillators in Colehill (at One Stop Shop, Colehill Memorial Hall and now the Reef)

About 2 weeks ago

This morning cllrs KD Johnson and Susan Cowsill will be representing #Colehill at the Dorset Association of Parish and Town Councils (#DAPTC) Towns and Larger Parishes Committee (it moves around, but today is in #Dorchester). ow.ly/qdtX30nNgl9
